text: All Out (2020) was a professional wrestling pay-per-view show made by All Elite Wrestling (AEW). It took place on September 5, 2020, mainly at the Daily's Place in Jacksonville, Florida. It was the second All Out event held by AEW. The main event saw Jon Moxley defeat MJF to keep the AEW International Championship. Moxley's finisher, the Paradigm Shift was banned, but he ended up hitting MJF with the Paradigm Shift anyways when the referee's back was turned. Moxley then got the pinfall victory. There was criticism for the match between Matt Hardy and Sammy Guevara. During the match, Hardy got speared off of a scissor lift by Guevara and was put through a table but he hit his head off of the concrete floor and appeared to be knocked out.
